Osbern (c. 1050 – c. 1090) was a Benedictine monk, hagiographer and musician, precentor of Christ Church, Canterbury.
He was born at Canterbury and brought up by Godric, who was dean from 1058–1080.
He became a monk, and later precentor of Christ Church, and was ordained by Archbishop Lanfranc of Canterbury (d. 1089).
He died probably between 1088 and 1093.
